item.title: Design
item.dc:creator: nich56
item.content:encoded:
Year 3 - Logo Design and Branding

During our Brand Identity Design module, we worked with live clients to produce a logo and new set of branding guidelines for the company. My client was a budgeting app called CU Button. It works alongside the credit union to provide a quick and secure money budgeting tool. This is my final logo design with some touchpoints to follow.                    

Year 3 - Dinosaur Illustrations

During one of our labs we were asked to create simplified dinosaur vectors in illustrator. This style has become widely popular and it's important to recap on basic flat shapes and styles.

 

Year 3 - Skull Illustrations

For this task, we had to perfect our pencil tool and blending tool skills. We had to create a wireframe of a buffalo's head using the blend tool. This can be so simple yet it looks like it could have been done with a complex 3D program.  

Year 2 - Typographic Poster

This assignment involved taking a well-known movie and recreating a poster of it using just typography. Mine is solely made up of words from the film in different colours to create an image of Superman. [caption id="attachment_22" align="aligncenter" width="437"] Superman[/caption]

Year 2 - Magazine Layout

For this assignment, we were asked to create and design a magazine of our choice. I decided to go for a baking magazine to grab the reader's attention with some beautiful images and colourful layouts. This has been my favourite assignment to date and I hope to get the opportunity to work with a real magazine in the future. [caption id="attachment_23" align="aligncenter" width="462"] Baker's Heaven Magazine[/caption] [sgmb id="1"]

item.title: Sound
item.dc:creator: nich56
item.content:encoded:
Year 2 - If Money Were No Object Voxpop

For this assignment, our task was to choose a question and record our classmates answers. My quesrion to my classmates was "If money were no object, what would you be doing right now?" We worked in teams to record answers but edited individually to see how our final piece differed. This tested our interview skills and editing skills to see how we could make it fun and unique. Tune in to hear my results.  

Year 2 - Growing Up in Business Podcast

I loved creating this piece as it helped me come to terms with life back when my parents were younger. I got to hear some stories that I hadn't heard before and had a few laughs along the way. I chose to interview my family and record their experiences from growing up in business in the 70s.  

Year 3 - Shallow Hal Scene Redub

The objective of this assignment was to gather all of your sound from licence free locations as well as your own original recordings to recreate a movie scene. I chose to redub one of my favourite comedy films which is Shallow Hal with Jack Black and put my own twist on it. Password: sound Shallow Hal Redub from Chloe Mc Nicholas on Vimeo. [sgmb id="1"]

item.title: Animation
item.dc:creator: nich56
item.content:encoded:
Year 1 - Where The Wild Things Are

This assignment was based around the 1963 children's book, "Where the Wild Things Are." We were asked to create our own portrayal of the character Beth and design a new "Wild Thing" called Emily. The next step was to design a jungle background in which our characters would roam. Finally, we were asked to create a 5-second snippet of the characters in motion which was done using Flash from the Adobe Suite. https://vimeo.com/194038057 [sgmb id="1"]

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: nich56
item.content:encoded: Determined third year Creative Digital Media student with an eye for detail and a hunger to succeed. Strong passion for graphic design, magazine design, social media and all things creative. I also have a good knowledge of sound design, website design and development and video production and post production. Why follow the crowd when you can be your own designer! "Creativity is intelligence having fun." - Albert Einstein Have a look at my Linkedin or download a copy of my CV.
